<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
No, this is not an anti-bard post, I have a few who are spectacular.  They know what to do when, and when not to do it.<P>Last night I met one I wanted to launch into space though.<P>Hunting in Velks hoping to get that final few kills to ding.  <P>We're loosing 2 tanks and pickings are getting slim so we pick up a bard (51+) and a 50 SK.<P>I knew the SK, recent addition to the guild, knows what to do, when to take orders and when to just kill.  And he's great at announcing his target a second or two before he hits so we know.<P>The bard had been playing his songs, we've had single and double pulls so I was out pulling.<P>In Velks I'm a kamakazi (sp?) puller.  Run to the very top and look.  As soon as I see a mob that's not engaged or not in someones camp below me,  tash, tash and run.  I dont run down the ramps though, you run and jump platform to platform.  As long as I'm  atleast 2lb below max weight I've never taken more than 1 red bub all the way bouncing down.<P>At once pull we get 3, not a problem but time to mez.  Mez one, no resist message, no stick message?  Try again.<P>"If you'd learn to read you'd see it's charmed" pipes in ye old bard.<P>Change targets and mez him.<P>"Scuse me. Don't do that.  I can't see your 1 line charmed message in the battle spam.  Do haste, mana and shielding songs, I don't care but dont charm or mez them"<P>Whole group agrees.<P>We get a couple more double and single pulls and life goes on. <P>I ding 58 a few mins later, tell them I need to run to the bank, I'd forgotten to bring my spells with me.  As slow as pulls are going and with a bard they'd be ok while I gate to thurg, bank and run back.  I'd mem the new spells once I got back.<P>Before I head out, the warrior who's helping pull brings 3 spiders.  I mez one, mez breaks...  I remez, no message... wtf???<P>"You charming again?"  and the charm message comes through.<P>"Hey guys, I'll sit here and buff,  Apparantly you don't need me to do CC as &lt;bard&gt; has it all under control"<P>Bard gets a bit snippy on me.  There's a short discussion about him stop playing with charm and do things like shield, mana and other usefull things since I'm actually trying to do CC.<P>It wouldn't have been so bad, but his pet would be on the wrong one.  The group would be on spider 1, he'd charm 2 and stick it on 3.<P>It'd do a bit of damage until his song would fail then then #2 and #3 would jump him and try to eat him.  As a result I have a mass of 3 spiders in 1 pile, all damaged and unable to target individually to re-mez.<P>After that pull I explained that apparantly there's no need for me.  Once I get my spells I'll not be coming back, they've got super bard.<P>I hope to group in OS or the likes with the 2 guild bards I know.  Both of them keep their mez/charm mem'd just in case, will kick in if I yell, but otherwise they let me do my job.  I like the ones who do the teamwork thing.  Amazing how well that works in a group.<P>--------------------<P>Blurem<BR>  Level 59 Dis-illusioned Illusionist
</FONT>
