<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well, it probably would have been better if the bard had mentioned that he was going to charm or perhaps talked to you about it but why do you think that a bard should not be allowed to charm?<P>On pulls of 4 and under a bard is just as good as an enchanter at crowd control.  Does this mean they should automatically wander in and do this job?  <P>A better question is: When you join a group with a bard in it, do you automatically start doing CC?  If the answer is yes, my question is why is it any different for you than it is for them?<P>You basically told the bard to take some of his most powerful songs and toss them in the trash bin because you were unable to work with him.<P>How would you like it if you joined a group and the bard told you to C2, haste and sit in the corner?  Yet that is essentially what you told him to do.<P>If he had a message stating that he was charming a mob and then did, there is really not much to complain about.<P>Try working with a bard to accomplish CC rather than assuming that the bard should automatically be relegated to a "buffing" position.  You apparently took great offense to being relegated to a buffing position yet you assume the bard should occupy one.<P>The sad fact of the matter is, when you left the group probably got along quite well with their "uber-bard".<P>Personally the best bards I have worked with are the ones that worked with me to accomplish CC rather than the ones that sat quietly in the corner singing the hp/mana regen song while watching TV.<P>A spectacular bard is not one who holds his charm and mezz song in reserve just in case you need his help ... <P>A spectacular bard, just like any member of a group is one that knows how to play his character to enhance the party rather than detract from it.<P>The power of an enchanter, similar to that of a bard, is the ability to alter our tactics to accomodate any situation.<P>It seems to me, in this case, that both of you need learn how to work within a party.<P>Regards,<P>--------------------<P>Zanithar TideBreaker<BR>Phantasmist <BR>Cazic Thule<BR>250 JewelCraft
</FONT>
