Ok, next time I'll just buff and melee, we know that Enchanters are a melee hybrid.<P>First up, I was in the group first, he joined later.  Second, his "charm" message was a one line "i've charmed %T" that he threw out in the middle of the fight.<P>He knew I was doing crowd control.<P>Durring the fight my job is CC.  Durring the fight, if there's no Chanter his job is CC.  Durring the fight With a chanter he has alot more useful spells, his haste, his shield spells, healing, damageshields.  <P>When he starts mezzing/charming durring combat he relegates me to sitting int he corner and buffing.  When his song breaks, I have no way of knowing what happened, what he's going to do about it and what he expects of me.  Should I try to remez the 2 additional creatures trying to eat him?  Am I going to mez the one he's trying to recharm?  Do I just sit and cast chain rune on him while he plays chanter?<P>When I group with another chanter (rare in exp, common on raids) we work out a system.  The lowest chanter with C2 does C2, next highest does Brilliance/enlighten, next does GoB.  If no epic, one does AQ/WR. <P>When mobs inc we break down who's gonna do "what" primarily.  In hate for instance, if a cleric, a rat and a Rev inc, I know I'm Rev First, another might be Cleric first and so on.  Once I lock down my target I look to see what's not locked and how's having problems.<P>I do not just break out the GFlux and have at it because it's an awsome tool and I can.  Any bets on how fast I'd be TL'd out?<P>--------------------<P>Blurem<BR>  Level 59 Dis-illusioned Illusionist
