If you have 3 mobs and you charm one add and have it go on the other then your effectivly doing the damage of two mobs(mobs are both hitting each other and your going to kill both afterward). Also this saves healer mana in the long run since the spiders are tanking each other. That bard was playing his class to best effect.<P>You could have assisted him by rooting what his pet was fighing and stunning when charm broke if you wanted to and this would have been more effective then mezzing everything and letting the group soak up all the damage.<P> Ideally the bard should have talked to you before charming since it would require you to change your tactics. He needs to convince others to work with him rather then ignoring them. Trying something different is fun but most people dont like to risk trying new things.<P> Spectacular bards keep their (and our) most powerful damage dealing spell in the game in reserve? Playing manasong doesn't sound very spectacular to me.
