And what I am saying is communication and compromise is the key.<P>If the bard wanted to charm then talk to him about it rather than simply saying:<BR>"Do not do that is interfers with me"<P>Then coming to this board and expecting me to say oh ya you were completely in the right ... evil evil bard how dare he charm!<P>On one hand you say "I like good bards" then you follow it up with they know not to do any form of CC as long as I am around.<P>Which leads me to believe you think a bard should know his role in a group which is basically not to interfer with you in any way and to shift his attention elsewhere.<P>I disagree, to me a good bard is one with whom I discuss what he wants to do and how to allow us to accomplish things together.<P>Most bards I group with are content to let me handle CC and I like to do CC so that makes me happy.<P>Some bards want to charm, if they can swing it ... mobs will drop faster at the expense of me having to pay a little more attention for a charm message and the occassional bounced mezz.  Fine.<P><BR>Merlinus:<BR>Thanks fer wandering by    <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  I learned a lot participating in the arguements on the bard board, but I did not enter that forum with the belief that enchanters should always have all aspects of CC and bards should always be backseated.<P>My arguements there were about where each class could best lend their efforts to maximize group efficiency.  <P>My opinion remains the same, take an enchanter away from Mezz duty and you are wasting him.  A bard has a lot of alternate abilities that he could be using.<P>As much as Blurem keeps trying to drag mezz into it, that was not his original complaint and it is not what I am addressing here.<P>His original complaint was about charming and I fully support a bards desire and right to utilize charming to enhance group efficiency    <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Mezzing is a whole different ball-game but that is not the basis of the arguement    <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>And yes, anyone that compares a rangers healing to a bards mezzing is sadly misinformed or simply being sarcastic.<P>Regards,<P>--------------------<P>Zanithar TideBreaker<BR>Phantasmist <BR>Cazic Thule<BR>250 JewelCraft
