I am with Zanithar on this one.  Bards can and will use charm.  I know if I was one I would. First, if the guy had a message saying he charmed the mob I am sorry but he is 100% right.  You should have read it.  That's why the litte text window is there.  If you can't read it adjust YOUR colors.  One line saying what he is doing in group chat is adequate, otherwise chat windows would be full of this kind of already partially annoying crap. Second, after the first little charm incident I'd then take it upon myself to figure out what each of us wants to do.  I may not be 58, but I know that everyone in the group is there to have fun and gain exp/levels/loot.  You can either divvy up the responsibilities and have some fun, or you can be a hard ass and tell someone who is playing a class with VERY similar abilities how to play because you are used to doing things a certain way.  How would you like the bard telling you what to do?  Being first in a group has no relevance really.  If a cleric joined a group with a druid the druid would not tell the cleric to play backup healer, hopefully they woud coordinate, which is what you should have done.  I personally think enchanters are #1 in the CC department, but bards can do a really good job at it as well and it's not my decision on how someone wants to play their character just as it's not their decision on how I play mine, but if I have a problem I'll work it out equitably, or I can graciously leave.<P>Azol<BR>56 Beguiler - Xegony
