*had to edit the original...read your post wrong*<P>Zanithar,<P>You've got it right, but I can keep 4 mobs mezzed.  Not just 3.  This is assuming no resists of course.  4 mezzed and 2 occupied fighting each other.  Bard songs have a duration of 12 seconds, with a few exceptions and mez seems to be one of these.  It doesn't last as long as charm (up to 18 seconds) but it often lasts longer than 12.<P>Realistically, including resists, I could probably lock down 4 mobs, and have 2 beating on me here and there.  Though our 53 mez song is a HUGE upgrade to our level 28 mez.  Since I've gotten it, I think I might be able to hold 5 with only one beating on me.   <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>4 mezzed, one charmed and beating on another (as long as it's out of range of PC's).  Sorry for the confusion.    <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Also, since you mention (I know you are joking, don't worry   <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0">) the enchanters = pure and good, bards = bad and evil, I think that people are working to stop this common belief.  Almost every bard has a enchanter alt, and lately many enchanters have come to the bard boards asking for advice with their bard alts.  It's good to see people trying the 'other side's' shoes on, so they can know what each other are talking about.<P>And I'm not really THAT evil...    <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>Ravenwing:<P>A bard can twist 4 songs maximum, period.  Due to the amount of time a song lasts, and the amount of time they take to start, 4 is the maximum possible.  The slightest bit of lag will reduce this to 3.  Sometimes, on really large raids, I can only consistantly twist 2 songs, because of lag.  Lag = Death to a bard.<P>I will note that there are weapons that proc song effects, and technically, if you count these 'weapon songs' you could twist up to 6 songs. (two weapons with procs)  Most weapons with these effects proc though (even the epic    <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0">), so you'll only have 6 songs up if they both proc.  The one exception to this (that I know of) is the Breath of Harmony which is clickable.<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21087" TARGET=_blank>Andrina Swiftfoot</A> Level 52 Half Elf Minstrel of Xegony's Anklebiter's Brigade<BR>Mukk Donalds Level 29 Ogre Warrior of the Anklebiter's Brigade
