Am I the only one that sees bards as the closest thing to an enchanter/warrior hybrid?<P>There are differences, but our skill areas are largely the same.  Working with a bard is much like working with another enchanter - communication and cooperation, and you're damn near unstoppable.<P>I think the bard in the initial story should have been more communicative at the start, as should have Blurem.  I don't think he was in the wrong for charming, I do think he was in the wrong for not talking about it first.  <P>Good communication is the difference between amazing success and horrifying disaster, 90% of the time.<P>--------------------<P><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=73730" TARGET=_blank>Teraine Mindsifter</A>, 51 Illusionist<BR><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=102562" TARGET=_blank>Gisselle S'Haine</A>, 33 Shadow Knight<BR>of <A HREF="http://www.smguild.com" TARGET=_blank>Socratic Method</A>, Xev
