<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Nice to see you come to the board with an open mind Knat.<P>He is a little optimistic about doing crowd control on a 7 mob pull as well as an enchanter can.<P>In my experience bards can do CC on 3 - 4 mobs as efficiently as an Enchanter.<P>Bards get armor, hp, cannot be interrupted, and can move while singing.  This pretty much makes up for the only advantage we have over them in CC ... AOE stun.<P>A better statement would be, given a bard and an enchanter in the group does it benefit the group more if the enchanter or bard does CC or if they work together to do CC?<P>A bard has all the tools we have, with the exception of stun, and a number of tools we do not to perform CC.  They are just as "designed" to do CC as we are.  The only difference is a bards efforts are generally best spent elsewhere when there is an enchanter in the group to enhance the group.<P>Regards,<P>--------------------<P>Zanithar TideBreaker<BR>Phantasmist <BR>Cazic Thule<BR>250 JewelCraft
</FONT>
